ðŸ”¹ What is TM1637?
TM1637 is an IC (chip) used to control 4-digit 7-segment LED displays.

It reduces the number of wires needed â€” only 2 pins (CLK and DIO) are used to control the display.

ðŸ”¹ Features:
4 digits, 7 segments per digit

Optional colon (used in time display)

Adjustable brightness

Only 2 Arduino pins needed

ðŸ”¹ Pin Description:
Pin	Function
VCC	Power (5V)
GND	Ground
DIO	Data I/O
CLK	Clock

ðŸ”¹ Arduino Connection:
TM1637	Arduino
VCC	5V
GND	GND
DIO	D2
CLK	D3

(You can change DIO and CLK pins in code.)

ðŸ”¹ Library Used:
ðŸ‘‰ TM1637TinyDisplay or TM1637Display

Install via:

Arduino IDE â†’ Sketch â†’ Include Library â†’ Manage Libraries

Search: TM1637TinyDisplay or TM1637Display

ðŸ”¹ Applications:
Digital clocks

Countdown timers

Sensor readings (like temperature, distance)

Scoreboards

code:
#include <TM1637TinyDisplay.h>

// Define connections
#define CLK 3   // Clock pin
#define DIO 2   // Data pin

TM1637TinyDisplay display(CLK, DIO);

void setup() {
  display.setBrightness(7);         // Brightness (0â€“7)
  display.showNumber(1234);         // Display number 1234
}

void loop() {
  // Nothing in loop
}
